title: PSYC 350A Psychological Aspects of Human Sexuality - PSYC ASP HM SEXL
description: Human sexuality from a biopsychological, behavioural, and psychosocial perspective.
prerequisites: Either (a) PSYC 100 or (b) all of PSYC 101, PSYC 102. (or (c) 6 credits of 200-level Psychology (but not 205 or 263).)
